<subSubSection id="C30E656BFFB5FF80FEEBE348FD592941" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAB36E0FFB5FF80FEEBE348FD592941" blockId="1.[264,1323,1108,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB5FF80FEEBE348FE5A2819" bold="true" box="[264,394,1108,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C144D63FFB5FF80FE77E348FDA9281A" box="[404,633,1108,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Potamobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shuar">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB5FF80FE77E348FDA9281A" box="[404,633,1108,1133]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">Potamobates shuar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D63FFB5FF80FC04E348FBAE281A" box="[999,1150,1108,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Potamobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchicaya">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB5FF80FC04E348FBAE281A" box="[999,1150,1108,1133]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">P. anchicaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having a single lateral spine on the right side of the male’s VIII abdominal segment (
<figureCitation id="132F2A65FFB5FF80FB18E360FEE028C9" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A, B" captionStartId="3.[264,368,860,884]" captionTargetBox="[470,1131,314,845]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[448,1145,306,871]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A, B: Potamobates shuar n. sp.; A: male genital segment, ventral view; B: male genital segment, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173727/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FEEBE3B8FEC828C9" box="[264,280,1188,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D63FFB5FF80FE80E3B8FE2728CA" box="[355,503,1188,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Potamobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchicaya">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB5FF80FE80E3B8FE2728CA" box="[355,503,1188,1213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">P. anchicaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the male has two lateral spines on the right side of the VIII abdominal segment. In the female 
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB5FF80FDF8E3D0FDAE2892" box="[539,638,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName id="4C144D63FFB5FF80FDF8E3D0FDAB2892" box="[539,635,1228,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Potamobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shuar">P. shuar</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the connexiva (
<figureCitation id="132F2A65FFB5FF80FCD9E3D0FCAC2891" box="[826,892,1228,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="2.[264,367,1745,1769]" captionTargetBox="[377,1217,608,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[370,1226,603,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: habitat of P. horvathi and P. anchicaya in locality Montalvo, La Mayronga (photo F. M. Buzzetti); B: habitat of P. shuar n. sp. in locality Bomboiza (photo P. Tirello); C: P. s h u a r n. sp. female abdomen in dorsal view (photo F. M. Buzzetti); D: P. s h u a r n. sp. male holotype (photo F. M. Buzzetti)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FC92E3D0FCAC2891" box="[881,892,1228,1254]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C) almost join at the level of the last two abdominal segments, whereas in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D63FFB5FF80FCEFE3E8FC78297A" box="[780,936,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Potamobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchicaya">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB5FF80FCEFE3E8FC78297A" box="[780,936,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">P. anchicaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
female the connexiva are well separated all along the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30E656BFFB5FF82FEDBE258FCF029EB" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAB36E0FFB5FF83FEDBE258FC072D41" blockId="1.[264,1323,1108,1900]" lastBlockId="2.[264,1321,284,550]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB5FF80FEDBE258FE022929" bold="true" box="[312,466,1348,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">Description:</emphasis>
Apterous male (
<typeStatus id="54AF8842FFB5FF80FD78E258FCCD2929" box="[667,797,1348,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">Holotypus</typeStatus>
): Ground color shining black, body covered with very dense, short, dark pubescence; head entirely creamy white except vertex and hind margin (
<figureCitation id="132F2A65FFB5FF80FE46E288FE3629D9" box="[421,486,1428,1454]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="2.[264,367,1745,1769]" captionTargetBox="[377,1217,608,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[370,1226,603,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: habitat of P. horvathi and P. anchicaya in locality Montalvo, La Mayronga (photo F. M. Buzzetti); B: habitat of P. shuar n. sp. in locality Bomboiza (photo P. Tirello); C: P. s h u a r n. sp. female abdomen in dorsal view (photo F. M. Buzzetti); D: P. s h u a r n. sp. male holotype (photo F. M. Buzzetti)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FE38E288FE3629D9" box="[475,486,1428,1454]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D); pronotum with wedge­shaped and anteriorly pointing creamy white marking medially (
<figureCitation id="132F2A65FFB5FF80FE0BE2A0FDFA29A1" box="[488,554,1468,1494]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="2.[264,367,1745,1769]" captionTargetBox="[377,1217,608,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[370,1226,603,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: habitat of P. horvathi and P. anchicaya in locality Montalvo, La Mayronga (photo F. M. Buzzetti); B: habitat of P. shuar n. sp. in locality Bomboiza (photo P. Tirello); C: P. s h u a r n. sp. female abdomen in dorsal view (photo F. M. Buzzetti); D: P. s h u a r n. sp. male holotype (photo F. M. Buzzetti)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FDFCE2A0FDFA29A1" box="[543,554,1468,1494]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D); mesonotum black with three differently shaped creamy white longitudinal stripes (
<figureCitation id="132F2A65FFB5FF80FE1DE2F8FD922989" box="[510,578,1508,1534]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="2.[264,367,1745,1769]" captionTargetBox="[377,1217,608,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[370,1226,603,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: habitat of P. horvathi and P. anchicaya in locality Montalvo, La Mayronga (photo F. M. Buzzetti); B: habitat of P. shuar n. sp. in locality Bomboiza (photo P. Tirello); C: P. s h u a r n. sp. female abdomen in dorsal view (photo F. M. Buzzetti); D: P. s h u a r n. sp. male holotype (photo F. M. Buzzetti)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FDD4E2F8FD922989" box="[567,578,1508,1534]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D); abdomen black, pleurae ventrally and all sternites creamy white. Bright pubescence present on propleurae, posterolateral corners of mesonotum, mesocoxae, lateral sides of metanotum, metacoxae, and lateral of abdominal tergites I–VII. Length of head (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FDF8E140FDF72A01" box="[539,551,1628,1654]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
) more than twice the narrowest interocular space (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FB98E140FB642A01" box="[1147,1204,1628,1654]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="0.35">0.35</number>
); width of eye 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FED9E19BFEB22AD6" box="[314,354,1671,1697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="0.5">0.5</number>
; eyes extending posteriorly 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FD52E198FD692AE5" box="[689,697,1668,1682]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FD21E18BFD1A2AD2" box="[706,714,1687,1701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="5.0">5</number>
onto propleura. Rostrum not reaching hind margin of prosternum. Pronotum wider (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FD64E1AEFD6C2ABB" box="[647,700,1714,1740]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="1.95">1.95</number>
) than long (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FCAAE1AEFC522ABB" box="[841,898,1714,1740]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="0.95">0.95</number>
). Mesonotum long if compared with thoracical segments 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FE1EE1C6FDE32A83" box="[509,563,1754,1780]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="2.85">2.85</number>
, widest across mosocoxae (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FC61E1C6FC7B2A83" box="[898,939,1754,1780]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="2.5">2.5</number>
). Metanotum short if compared with other thoracical segments 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FD60E01EFD692B6B" box="[643,697,1794,1820]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="0.85">0.85</number>
, widest across metacoxae (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FBE0E01EFBEC2B6B" box="[1027,1084,1794,1820]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="2.45">2.45</number>
). Abdomen short if compared with whole body, its length excluding genital segments 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FBFCE036FB852B33" box="[1055,1109,1834,1860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="2.45">2.45</number>
, genital segments longer than abdomen (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FDFFE04EFD852B1B" box="[540,597,1874,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="3.15">3.15</number>
). Tergites II–V subequal in length (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FBEFE04EFBBA2B1B" box="[1036,1130,1874,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3</number>
), tergite I 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB5FF80FB0DE04EFAF42B1B" box="[1262,1316,1874,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="52" value="0.45">0.45</number>
, tergite VI 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB6FF83FE63E600FE662D41" box="[384,438,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="0.35">0.35</number>
, tergite VII 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB6FF83FDA0E600FDBB2D41" box="[579,619,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, tergite VIII the longest (
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB6FF83FC71E600FC1B2D41" box="[914,971,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="2.15">2.15</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36E0FFB6FF83FEDBE658FEB12DF1" blockId="2.[264,1321,284,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Tergite VII with angulated connexiva, these not produced and ventrally emarginated in middle.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36E0FFB6FF83FEDBE688FC2B2E51" blockId="2.[264,1321,284,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
Tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="132F2A65FFB6FF83FE31E688FDFE2DD9" box="[466,558,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A, B" captionStartId="3.[264,368,860,884]" captionTargetBox="[470,1131,314,845]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[448,1145,306,871]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A, B: Potamobates shuar n. sp.; A: male genital segment, ventral view; B: male genital segment, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173727/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB6FF83FDEBE688FDC72DD9" box="[520,535,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
A
</figureCitation>
) modified, right lateral side bearing single stout spine rising from more or less defined lobe. In dorsal view hind margin of this tergite bent, wright side longer than left. Pygophore rotated 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB6FF83FD57E6F8FD032D89" box="[692,723,484,510]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="90.0">90</number>
° on left, proctiger bearing long, apically widened lateral process on left side, this visible in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="132F2A65FFB6FF83FC73E510FC3E2E51" box="[912,1006,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A, B" captionStartId="3.[264,368,860,884]" captionTargetBox="[470,1131,314,845]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[448,1145,306,871]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A, B: Potamobates shuar n. sp.; A: male genital segment, ventral view; B: male genital segment, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173727/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDC24C7FFB6FF83FC25E510FC062E51" box="[966,982,524,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
A
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6B6668FFB6FF83FEEBE1CDFE462B2D" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173726/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" targetBox="[377,1217,608,1718]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BAB36E0FFB6FF83FEEBE1CDFE462B2D" blockId="2.[264,1323,1745,1882]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB6FF83FEEBE1CDFE592A9E" bold="true" box="[264,393,1745,1769]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
A: habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D63FFB6FF83FDFFE1CDFD402A9F" box="[540,656,1745,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Potamobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB6FF83FDFFE1CDFD402A9F" box="[540,656,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">P. horvathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D63FFB6FF83FD20E1CDFC992A9F" box="[707,841,1745,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Potamobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchicaya">
<emphasis id="B960EAF2FFB6FF83FD20E1CDFC992A9F" box="[707,841,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">P. anchicaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in locality Montalvo, La Mayronga (photo F. M. Buzzetti); B: habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D63FFB6FF83FDCBE1EAFDAF2B7A" box="[552,639,1782,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Potamobates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shuar" status="n. sp.">
